<item>
            <title>[FLINK-15301] Flink Kinesis AsyncRecordEmitter needs to handle unchecked exception gracefully</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-15301</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, any runTime exception encountered inside the `AsyncRecordEmitter.emitRecordAndUpdateState()` function could cause the thread to exit silently. Flink job would continue to run, but the stopped record emitter would subsequently cause Kinesis data consumption to stall.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The AsyncRecordEmitter need to catch unchecked exception, log errors, and perhaps trigger job restart subsequently.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
